"sysstat" is a collection of performance monitoring tools for Linux.
The package is intended to be used by system administrators and
power-users.

The package contains the following tools:

- sar: collects and reports system activity information;
- sadf: displays data in various formats (standard output, XML,
  HTML);
- iostat: reports CPU utilization and disk I/O statistics;
- pidstat: reports process statistics (CPU, memory, file system
